Code 
cellcounts = as.data.frame(table(obj_orig_meta$orig.ident))
cellcounts$Group = obj_orig_meta[,qc_groupby][match(cellcounts$Var1, obj_orig_meta$orig.ident)]
ggplot(cellcounts, aes(x = Group, y = Freq)) + geom_jitter(width = 0.1) + lims(y = c(0,NA)) +
  labs(x = "", y = "Cell count")

Quality control and filtering

We use four variables to compare the quality of each sample: Number of unique genes (ânFeature_RNAâ), number of UMI counts (ânCounts_RNAâ), % of mitochondrial RNA in the sample (âpercent.mitoâ) and % of ribosomal RNA in the sample (âpercent.riboâ). The quality control metrics are shown for each sample before and after filtering.
